3974	\begin{lemma}[Continuity of the over-site equivalence]
3975	  \label{lem:overEquivalence_isContinuous}
3976	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Opens.overEquivalence_functor_coverPreserving,
3977	    AlgebraicGeometry.Opens.overEquivalence_inverse_coverPreserving,
3978	    AlgebraicGeometry.Opens.overEquivalence_functor_isContinuous,
3979	    AlgebraicGeometry.Opens.overEquivalence_inverse_isContinuous}
3980	  \uses{lem:overEquivalence_mathlib}
3981	  Both functors of the over-site equivalence
3982	  \((\operatorname{Opens} T).\operatorname{over} U \simeq \operatorname{Opens} U\) of
3983	  Lemma~\ref{lem:overEquivalence_mathlib} are cover-preserving and continuous for the respective
3984	  Grothendieck topologies of pointwise covers. Their continuity is the site-theoretic input required
3985	  by the site-equivalence transport of step B3.
3986	\end{lemma}
3987	\begin{proof}
3988	  \uses{lem:overEquivalence_mathlib}
3989	  The opens Grothendieck topology is the pointwise-cover predicate; the over-topology unfolds via
3990	  the membership criterion for over-topologies, and the subspace-versus-image point correspondence is
3991	  the obvious \(\langle x', hx'\rangle\) / underlying-value bookkeeping, giving cover-preservation of
3992	  each functor. Continuity then follows from cover-preservation together with the cover-density,
3993	  local-fullness and local-faithfulness that hold automatically for the fully-faithful, essentially
3994	  surjective functors of an equivalence.
3995	\end{proof}
